    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{1, 12, -17, -3, -11, -5\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{1 + 12 + (-17) + (-3) + (-11) + (-5)}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{1 + 12 - 17 - 3 - 11 - 5}{6}\n= \\frac{-23}{6} \\approx -3.8333\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Subtract the mean from each data point and square the result\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(1 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (4.8333)^2 \\approx 23.377 \\\\\n(12 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (15.8333)^2 \\approx 250.777 \\\\\n(-17 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (-13.1667)^2 \\approx 173.377 \\\\\n(-3 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (0.8333)^2 \\approx 0.694 \\\\\n(-11 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (-7.1667)^2 \\approx 51.377 \\\\\n(-5 - (-3.8333))^2 &= (-1.1667)^2 \\approx 1.361 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared differences\n\n$$\n23.377 + 250.777 + 173.377 + 0.694 + 51.377 + 1.361 \\approx 499.582\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 4: Divide by $ n - 1 $ (where $ n = 6 $)\n\n$$\n\\text{Variance} = \\frac{499.582}{6 - 1} = \\frac{499.582}{5} \\approx"
